 style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Foss, Sonja K (1996). <i>Rhetorical Criticism: Exploration and Practice</i>. Prospect Heights, IL: Waveland Press. p.&#160;26.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Rhetorical+Criticism%3A+Exploration+and+Practice&amp;rft.place=Prospect+Heights%2C+IL&amp;rft.pages=26&amp;rft.pub=Waveland+Press&amp;rft.date=1996&amp;rft.aulast=Foss&amp;rft.aufirst=Sonja+K&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANeo-Aristotelianism\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Wichelns, Herbert A. (1925). <i>\"The Literary Criticisms of Oratory,\" in Studies in Rhetoric and Public Speaking in Honor of James A. Winans</i>. New York: Century. pp.&#160;181\u2013183.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%22The+Literary+Criticisms+of+Oratory%2C%22+in+Studies+in+Rhetoric+and+Public+Speaking+in+Honor+of+James+A.+Winans&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pages=181-183&amp;rft.pub=Century&amp;rft.date=1925&amp;rft.aulast=Wichelns&amp;rft.aufirst=Herbert+A.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANeo-Aristotelianism\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Klyn, Mark S. (1968). <i>\"Toward a Pluralistic Rhetorical Criticism,\" in Essays on Rhetorical Criticism</i>. New York: Random House. p.&#160;154.</cit